PEOPLE v. WAY. Appeal from the Court of Sessions of the County of Napa.

Edgarton & Hopkins for Appellant.

Attorney General for Respondent.

Terry, C. J., delivered the opinion of the Court—

Baldwin, J., and Field, J., concurring.

The plea of former conviction is not supported by the evidence, and was properly overruled.

The objection that the evidence did not warrant the judgment is equally unsupported by the record.

Judgment affirmed.
